1
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,800
Master Jiang Ziliu

2
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:08,039
was specially invited by our Provincial Museum.

3
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,360
He insisted on using paper from your Xuan family.

4
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:13,160
He thinks highly of the Xuan paper you make.

5
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,920
You're the 35th-generation heir of Xuan Family Xuan Paper,

6
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,960
and a National Intangible Cultural Heritage Inheritor.

7
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:25,520
How many Xuan paper contests were held?

8
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,320
And this plaque,

9
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,560
it's never once been taken down.

10
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,760
Truly, a thousand-year Xuan family,

11
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:34,320
a thousand-year Xuan paper!

12
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:38,280
Rotten wood withers,

13
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,640
and beauty fades with age.

14
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,200
Often, a great reputation

15
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,000
is hard to live up to.

16
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:48,440
How can he speak like that?

17
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,280
Brother Yongnian,

18
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,920
tell me, what kind of paper

19
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:53,320
truly counts as fine paper?

20
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,720
Master Jiang asks

21
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:01,000
what makes a good sheet of Xuan paper.

22
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:03,920
Well, the ancestors of Xuan papermaking

23
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,280
settled that long ago.

24
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:07,320
Of course,

25
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,720
to each their own taste.

26
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,640
It's not up to us papermakers to decide,

27
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:13,880
but rather

28
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,360
up to those who use it.

29
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:22,200
Five Shades of Ink,

30
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:25,520
thick, light, dry, parched, and wet.

31
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:28,720
Thick, like midnight dew condensing;

32
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:33,080
light, like misty rain veiling gauze.

33
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,760
Saturated, it bears a mountain's weight;

34
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:40,760
spread out, it reveals five-hued mysteries.

35
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:45,520
Parched, it splits like metallic sinews;

36
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:50,080
Moist, it bathes in Jiangnan's mist.

37
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,240
Ink seeps into the grain,

38
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,560
ripples spreading layer by layer,

39
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,960
like a hazy moon staining the river,

40
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,240
or a star falling into a pool.

41
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,400
This single stroke

42
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:01,000
holds all the cycles of yin and yang.

43
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,120
Did you understand any of that?

44
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,080
Nope.

45
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:07,960
Brother Yongnian,

46
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,000
Master,

47
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,320
am I right?

48
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:14,880
The master's poem is surely a fine one.

49
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,720
I was talking about paper.

50
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,240
Then it's surely fine paper.

51
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,120
We'll only know once we've tested it.

52
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:25,080
Master Jiang's Four-foot Ribbed Extra-Pure Single Xuan Paper

53
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:26,200
is finished.

54
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:31,920
Good.

55
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,560
Master, please inspect the paper.

56
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:35,960
Let's go.

57
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:47,960
Master!

58
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:48,880
Master!

59
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,920
It's fine, it's fine, it's fine.

60
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,600
Master!

61
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:00,720
It's nothing, it's nothing.

62
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:02,120
You all right?

63
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:02,680
Master.

64
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:03,600
I'm fine.

65
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,320
I've missed you like crazy!

66
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,440
A new hot spring just opened near us,

67
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,200
and it's amazing.

68
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,240
I'll take you for a soak in a bit.

69
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,520
Stop fooling around!

70
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:13,800
Master Jiang is here on business.

71
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,640
How can you take him to bathe?

72
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,560
But Master loves this kind of thing!

73
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:18,640
We'll talk about it later.

74
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,080
Let's go.

75
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:22,520
Hurry up!

76
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:24,000
Get out.

77
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:26,680
Mom.

78
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,040
Taozi.

79
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:36,800
Who's that guy?

80
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,520
Xuan Yongnian's son,

81
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,360
Xuan Yan.

82
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,920
This four-foot sheet Master scooped

83
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,320
You won't find its equal anywhere else.

84
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,560
Let's see what he has to say now.

85
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,880
This sheet Yongnian made

86
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:19,640
truly lives up to the old ancestral saying.

87
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:23,280
Light as a cicada's wing, white as snow;

88
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:26,480
soft as silk, without a sound.

89
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,600
Master Jiang's choice of subject

90
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,440
flows with the ink and with his heart.

91
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:38,000
Truly breathtaking.

92
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,320
Great paper is just great paper.

93
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,880
The painting turns out entirely different.

94
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,000
Truly an ever-changing charm of ink.

95
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,760
Ever-changing charm of ink, indeed.

96
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:53,000
Though freshly dried with rawness in it,

97
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:53,920
but look here,

98
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:57,120
where dark, it bears a thousand pounds;

99
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:00,600
where pale, it stirs the cloud shadows.

100
00:07:08,760 --> 00:07:09,440
What a pity.

101
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,440
Such a pity.

102
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:19,120
Please enlighten us, Master Jiang.

103
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:20,680
Come.

104
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:23,440
Stand this painting up.

105
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:27,760
Let Brother Yongnian reflect on it deeply.

106
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,680
Your paper is like this withered lotus,

107
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,280
its stems dry and ready to snap,

108
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,520
wind sweeping away the tattered leaves.

109
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:38,600
A pond aged by time should retire in peace.

110
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,120
It's time you stepped down.

111
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,240
Or you'll ruin a lifetime's reputation,

112
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,880
and become a laughingstock.

113
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:47,640
Master Jiang,

114
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:50,480
we've toured all around Peach Blossom Town.

115
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:53,760
Master Xuan's craftsmanship is unrivaled.

116
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:54,880
So how about we just...

117
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,520
Enough.

118
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:56,520
You saw it too.

119
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:58,120
Your master is definitely off today.

120
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,560
Go talk some sense into him.

121
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:00,960
Yet not a single good sheet came out.

122
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:01,920
One is my master,

123
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:02,880
the other is my dad.

124
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:03,680
Who am I supposed to persuade?

125
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,440
Just try.

126
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,920
A blind man checking a watch—a waste.

127
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:07,440
Mom,

128
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,920
don't get involved.

129
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:09,520
Alright.

130
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:11,640
These days,

131
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,880
finding a truly great sheet of paper

132
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,880
is genuinely difficult.

133
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,440
Even here,

134
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:20,320
with thousand-year Xuan paper and family.

135
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:23,760
What are you saying?

136
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:26,440
Let's go.

137
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,000
Master Jiang.

138
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:29,680
Master Jiang.

139
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,440
You said at the thousand-year Xuan Family,

140
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,760
you can't find a single good sheet.

141
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:34,679
So what exactly does good paper look like?

142
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:35,400
Yeah.

143
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,240
Don't be rash.

144
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,480
I'm sorry, Master Jiang.

145
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,240
She's new, she doesn't understand.

146
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,320
Fine, no need to say more.

147
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,240
Young lady, let me give you a poem.

148
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:43,919
Rain enters sand traces, ink darkens naturally;

149
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:47,120
myriad cloud patterns embrace sea and sky.

150
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,880
Can you explain clearly

151
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,560
what it takes for ink to darken naturally?

152
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,520
Young lady, you...

153
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,000
I just transferred to Peach Blossom Town.

154
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,320
I don't know much about Xuan paper yet.

155
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,520
But I do know

156
00:08:57,640 --> 00:09:00,320
the Xuan family is a millennium-old lineage.

157
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,640
Xuan Family paper

158
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:03,600
is globally renowned and widely praised.

159
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,880
I think the comment you just made

160
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:05,560
wasn't quite appropriate.

161
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,320
Of course,

162
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:07,520
if

163
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,440
you can point out the specific problem,

164
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,480
I'm sure Master Xuan can improve it.

165
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,120
You don't even understand.

166
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:12,640
So,

167
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:13,800
is it a scooping problem,

168
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,480
a drying problem,

169
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,240
or a material problem?

170
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,200
Yeah.

171
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:18,800
No, this...

172
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,200
Young lady, who are you?

173
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:21,640
Where's this girl from?

174
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,360
What does she do?

175
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,080
She's from Secretary Peng.

176
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:25,800
She was assigned to accompany us.

177
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,760
I'm new to the Economic Development Office.

178
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:28,680
My name is Lin Yiran.

179
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,760
Lin Yiran.

180
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:30,880
Young lady,

181
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,680
let me tell you,

182
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,120
when it comes to paper...

183
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:32,880
Master Jiang.

184
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:35,600
As for young Lin,

185
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:38,120
she's a young girl.

186
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:41,400
You should speak a bit more gently.

187
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:43,120
Your coming to my place today

188
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:46,240
and your actions really shocked me.

189
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,320
If you think our temple is too small

190
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,880
to hold a great Buddha like you,

191
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,800
then you should

192
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:53,560
go find yourself a bigger temple.

193
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:55,640
Really.

194
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:59,000
Otherwise, we can't afford to have you.

195
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,480
Stop, stop recording.

196
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,360
Xuan Yongnian,

197
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,120
I've used your family's paper for decades.

198
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:16,880
Now I don't even have the right to speak?

199
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,160
That's absolutely not the case.

200
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:24,320
You're our customer,

201
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:26,840
and what's more,

202
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,000
you're a renowned expert.

203
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,520
Just a word or gesture from you

204
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,120
can make our tiny private business

205
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,520
either thrive

206
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,200
or die.

207
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,880
If you really can't stand us here,

208
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,960
then you go your way,

209
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,640
and I'll go mine.

210
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,280
What's that supposed to mean?

211
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,880
Are you trying to kick me out?

212
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:50,160
Master, Master, Master.

213
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:51,120
You first—

214
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,520
Please calm down, calm down.

215
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,640
What now?

216
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:54,520
Dad.

217
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:55,440
Dad.

218
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:56,680
My master is a grand master.

219
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,400
He has to put on airs when he speaks.

220
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,640
That's what makes him a master.

221
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,120
You have to understand that.

222
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:01,840
See, like this—

223
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,720
You little brat, what are you saying?

224
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,640
Master, Master.

225
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,120
My dad, when he talks,

226
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,320
he's got a bit of a sharp tongue.

227
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,720
His mouth is really foul.

228
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,040
All the neighbors know that.

229
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:10,960
That's why nobody likes him.

230
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:11,520
He's terrible with people.

231
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:11,880
Exactly.

232
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,480
You're awful with people, you know?

233
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,480
Who does things like that?

234
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:14,840
Right, right, right.

235
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:15,360
Isn't that so?

236
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,320
I'll beat you to death!

237
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:17,080
Dad!

238
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:17,640
Mom!

239
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,200
What are you doing?

240
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:19,680
Old Xuan.

241
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,440
What a rotten brat.

242
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,200
He may be a brat,

243
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,840
but his master is the one who taught him.

244
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,880
You can't blame this on me.

245
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:31,840
A tadpole can never become a phoenix.

246
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,000
No matter what,

247
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,640
he's still your own flesh and blood.

248
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:37,920
Master, Master.

249
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,640
This Jiang Ziliu...

250
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,560
I was a bit harsh today,

251
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,520
but I just wanted to knock sense into him.

252
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,200
Why run such a big operation all alone?

253
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,280
An old horse pulling a heavy cart,

254
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:05,640
how long can he keep pulling?

255
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:06,480
Can he even manage it?

256
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:07,880
Rather than doing this,

257
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,200
just lay off the workers you need to.

258
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,600
Keep just one vat,

259
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:12,760
and calmly,

260
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:15,280
make some really fine paper.

261
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,160
Wouldn't that be better?

262
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,760
I invited you all this way

263
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:18,880
for exactly that reason.

264
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,480
The plan was,

265
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,720
you'd give him a good scolding,

266
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,560
and he'd back down.

267
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:24,520
Who would've thought

268
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,120
some troublemaker would show up

269
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,120
and mess the whole thing up like this?

270
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:29,880
If she's the troublemaker,

271
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:30,760
then what are we?

272
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:31,880
No, no.

273
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,480
That's not what I meant, Master.

274
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:34,440
Please don't be angry.

275
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,640
She's just a hothead.

276
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,000
Right, right, a hothead.

277
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:37,760
All right.

278
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,480
Xuan Yan,

279
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:41,720
as your master, I've done all I can.

280
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:44,600
But this world is no pure land,

281
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,240
everyone has their own troubles.

282
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:49,040
You know your father's temper.

283
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:50,720
If it really doesn't work out,

284
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,240
just let him be.

285
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,880
That's all we can do for now.

286
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,040
I'm leaving.

287
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:57,480
Let me see you off.

288
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,760
Master Jiang,

289
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:01,840
how did it go?

290
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,040
Did you finish talking?

291
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:03,840
Yes, we did.

292
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:04,880
Then let's go.

293
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:05,520
Let's go.

294
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:05,960
All right, goodbye.

295
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,520
Master Jiang, take care.

296
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,240
Goodbye.

297
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,600
Master,

298
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:09,400
take it slow.

299
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,480
Take care of yourself.

300
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,440
Look after your father.

301
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:24,400
Hold on there, hero.

302
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:25,880
What is it, Xuan Yan?

303
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:30,080
May I ask who this lovely lady is?

304
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:32,280
I'm just a person.

305
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:36,000
But let me give you a word of advice.

306
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,840
A thousand-year legacy isn't easy.

307
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,520
But if...

308
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,760
there's a spendthrift in the family,

309
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:44,000
he could ruin that thousand-year heritage.

310
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,640
Who are you calling a spendthrift?

311
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:46,480
Enough.

312
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,040
Let's go.

313
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,360
Calling me a spendthrift...

314
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,120
Interesting.

315
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,560
This Lin Yiran...

316
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,840
isn't fit for the Economic Development Office.

317
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:09,320
Dealing with people,

318
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:11,400
she doesn't even have basic tact.

319
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:12,720
Director Liao,

320
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:15,520
hosting Master Jiang is a crucial task.

321
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,520
Didn't I tell you to arrange it yourself?

322
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,640
How does it always end up

323
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:20,000
becoming Lin Yiran's problem?

324
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:21,280
Secretary Peng,

325
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:25,520
two Xuan paper workshops dumped wastewater

326
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:26,480
and got caught as examples.

327
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,000
Director Liu of the Environmental Bureau

328
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,600
expects my rectification report at 8 a.m.

329
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,720
You're also pushing me on the video page.

330
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,880
Where would I find the time?

331
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:37,360
This Lin Yiran,

332
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,600
isn't she supposed to be very capable?

333
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,200
It's not about ability.

334
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:42,040
It's just...

335
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,160
her EQ is too low.

336
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:46,400
We invited Master Jiang to promote us,

337
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,760
and what does she do?

338
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,440
She offended him completely in one go.

339
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,520
The Economic Development Office bears

340
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,160
Peach Blossom Town's economic development.

341
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:55,240
Time is tight, the load is heavy.

342
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:57,120
If she keeps stirring things up like this,

343
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:59,040
we really can't get any work done.

344
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:00,560
Director, Secretary,

345
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,080
Yiran has only been here for two weeks.

346
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,880
She's not used to our system yet.

347
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:07,320
It's understandable, isn't it?

348
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:08,640
She has no intention of adapting.

349
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,640
We're the ones adapting to her.

350
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:11,880
We have to give young people...

351
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:12,880
Secretary Peng!

352
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,400
She's gone viral! Viral!

353
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,000
Who's viral? What happened?

354
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:17,840
Lin Yiran.

355
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,000
Lin Yiran has gone viral.

356
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:19,400
Take a look.

357
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,880
You said you can't find good paper here.

358
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:23,880
Sixty thousand likes.

359
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,520
Thirty thousand shares.

360
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:26,640
We're done for.

361
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:27,400
Can you clearly explain

362
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:29,120
what "ink darkens naturally" really means?

363
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,840
The Xuan family has a millennium legacy.

364
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,880
Xuan family paper is universally praised,

365
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:34,640
renowned both at home and abroad.

366
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,480
Who is this?

367
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,760
This has really gone viral.

368
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:39,240
I'm new to the Economic Development Office.

369
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,000
My name is Lin Yiran.

370
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:41,640
A pond aged by time.

371
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,160
Master Jiang has used Old Xuan's paper

372
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:43,840
for so many years.

373
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,600
How could he start talking nonsense now?

374
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,920
Finding a good piece of paper these days

375
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,600
is really so hard.

376
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,000
Even here,

377
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:51,640
with thousand-year Xuan paper and family.

378
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:52,040
Look at this.

379
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:53,320
With these view counts,

380
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,240
the old man will be furious if he sees it.

381
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,720
This will ruin the old man, this will.

382
00:15:58,520 --> 00:15:59,000
You don't even understand.

383
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,720
So,

384
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:01,520
is it a problem with the scooping,

385
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:02,120
or with the drying?

386
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:03,960
Making such a fuss like this

387
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,600
isn't good for that girl.

388
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,600
Not good for her.

389
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:09,120
Clashing with my master like this,

390
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,360
it's likely bad for Peach Blossom Town.

391
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,280
I'm a new hire.

392
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,160
And you're still laughing?

393
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:14,640
Have a conscience.

394
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,400
That girl is speaking up for us.

395
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:17,240
Yes.

396
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:18,720
I don't want to laugh either.

397
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:20,520
But my master,

398
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:21,960
he just called her a hothead.

399
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:22,920
Son.

400
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,520
Isn't Director Liao your former teacher?

401
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:27,000
Go talk to him.

402
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,240
Don't make things hard for that girl.

403
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:28,880
Okay, okay, okay.

404
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:29,440
Go, go, go.

405
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:31,360
Where are you going?

406
00:16:31,840 --> 00:16:32,960
I'm going to discuss some business.

407
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,360
You have actual business to discuss?

408
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:36,240
Even a dung beetle

409
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,560
can find a place to roll its ball.

410
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:38,360
What's wrong with me?

411
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:38,640
Enough.

412
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:39,520
Can't I have any real business?

413
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,000
They're waiting for your bagged pulp.

414
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:41,800
They need it this afternoon.

415
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:43,880
I know. I sent Zhang Du to do it.

416
00:16:43,880 --> 00:16:44,640
I asked him to help me.

417
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:47,120
Since when do you get to assign the work?

418
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,520
I wouldn't dare assign anything.

419
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:52,160
We call it mutual help and solidarity.

420
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:52,840
I'm off, Mom.

421
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:59,000
A spoiled child turns unfilial, a rich field yields withered rice.

422
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,160
You nitpick your son all day long.

423
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,160
With all that time,

424
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:02,960
you should think hard about

425
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,319
how we're going to pay wages this month.

426
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,800
Doesn't Teacher Chen have a big order?

427
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,480
He placed the order, yes,

428
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,000
but the money hasn't arrived.

429
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:11,520
Same old rule:

430
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,400
payment on delivery.

431
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:15,400
Don't you worry.

432
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:20,280
Taozi.

433
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,560
You finally picked up.

434
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,599
Director Liao wants you back right now.

435
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:26,520
Secretary Peng is furious this time.

436
00:17:26,839 --> 00:17:27,599
He says it's caused our town

437
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:29,240
serious negative impact.

438
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,400
Everyone's discussing what to do now.

439
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:32,360
I'm telling you,

440
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,960
they might hold someone accountable.

441
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:37,160
Something came up with my mom.

442
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,520
I really can't get away.

443
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:39,440
No, listen,

444
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:41,760
sis, you've got to come back.

445
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:42,720
I'm telling you,

446
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,240
the director's still angry.

447
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,920
The secretary just said he'd reassign you.

448
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,040
If you don't come back soon,

449
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,040
this is going to blow up.

450
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,080
Fine, I got it.

451
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:00,600
Sister Jiang.

452
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,600
Can we... can we talk for a minute?

453
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:03,880
What's there to talk about?

454
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,880
I grab a meal, she says I take too long.

455
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:08,600
She gets up seven or eight times a night.

456
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:09,600
I didn't say a word.

457
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:11,880
I sleep barely two or three hours a day.

458
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,680
This afternoon I just dozed off for a bit,

459
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:16,760
and your mom says I sleep all day long.

460
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:17,760
Hold on.

461
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:18,760
Sister Jiang, Sister Jiang.

462
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:19,400
Sister Jiang.

463
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:21,280
Look, we've always gotten along well,

464
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:21,640
right?

465
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:22,880
Just give me two days.

466
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:24,320
Once I find someone, you can leave, okay?

467
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,360
We've already had it out.

468
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,920
What's the point of staying?

469
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:28,000
I've already lined up my next job.

470
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,120
You'd better hurry and find someone.

471
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:30,240
No, Sister Jiang, Sister Jiang.

472
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:44,240
Slow down.

473
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:46,080
The two packs of tissues I just bought,

474
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,040
she took them all.

475
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:49,480
Go get them back.

476
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:51,760
You won't go, huh?

477
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:52,920
Then I'll go myself.

478
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:54,160
Okay, okay, Mom.

479
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:54,880
Slow, slow down.

480
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:55,760
Mom, listen,

481
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:56,480
if you don't want to keep her,

482
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:57,840
can't you just tell me directly?

483
00:18:57,960 --> 00:18:59,040
You just say "she's done,"

484
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,560
where am I supposed to find someone?

485
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:03,080
Can't you just take two days off?

486
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,720
What's wrong with taking care of me?

487
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:06,400
Mom,

488
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:09,160
you made me take the civil service exam.

489
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:11,240
Do you know how exhausting my job is?

490
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:12,040
You...

491
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,240
I can't be bothered to argue with you.

492
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,200
There's an emergency at work.

493
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:18,920
You...

494
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:21,280
Fine, fine, fine.

495
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:22,320
Go, just go, go.

496
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:23,880
I don't need anyone.

497
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:24,960
I don't need a caregiver.

498
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,600
I can't even rely on my own daughter.

499
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,600
Just leave me here all by myself.

500
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:31,960
My life or death is none of your business.

501
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:32,840
Get out of my way.

502
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:38,240
Young lady,

503
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:41,080
she just had surgery, so she's like this.

504
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:42,920
Don't take it to heart.

505
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,320
I happen to know a caregiver.

506
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:47,240
She's pretty good.

507
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:49,000
Want me to ask for you?

508
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:50,560
Oh, thank you so much.

509
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,760
Thank you, ma'am.

510
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:52,760
All right.

511
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,280
Go check on your mom.

512
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:55,760
Right, thank you, thanks.

513
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:02,880
This Lin Yiran,

514
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,320
we can't even reach her by phone.

515
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,880
This is tough for you to handle.

516
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,240
Who'd have thought this would blow up?

517
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:35,920
Lin Yiran.

518
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:37,800
Why did you hang up on me?

519
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:38,680
Are you my boss,

520
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:39,840
or am I yours?

521
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:41,360
I had too much going on.

522
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:42,000
I'm sorry.

523
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:43,760
Are you living up to your job,

524
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:45,080
and to your responsibilities?

525
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,720
Do you have any idea how much trouble

526
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:47,400
you've caused us?

527
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:49,120
Is this really my fault?

528
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,040
What did you say?

529
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:53,600
Director Liao,

530
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,560
it was precisely out of responsibility

531
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,280
that I corrected Jiang Ziliu face-to-face.

532
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:57,960
We can't just let him

533
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,760
smear our town's Xuan paper industry.

534
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,600
So you think you did nothing wrong?

535
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:05,960
The video caused serious negative impact.

536
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,200
Isn't that a fact?

537
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:09,600
First of all,

538
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,080
I believe the negative impact of this

539
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:13,760
was caused by Jiang Ziliu saying

540
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:14,840
Peach Blossom Town can't make good paper,

541
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,000
not from me pushing back at him.

542
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:17,200
Second,

543
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:20,880
the top priority right now is to address

544
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,760
the fallout caused by Jiang Ziliu's

545
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:23,880
irresponsible remarks.

546
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,400
Whether I bear responsibility,

547
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:27,840
can't that wait until

548
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:29,240
the negative impact is resolved,

549
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:30,480
and then hold me accountable?

550
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:31,680
I think it wouldn't be too late.

551
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,600
Let's set aside the blame talk for now.

552
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:35,320
Lin Yiran,

553
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,240
so how do you think we should fix this?

554
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,280
Then I'll offer three suggestions.

555
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:40,160
First,

556
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,000
confront Jiang Ziliu immediately.

557
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:44,480
He's already damaged Peach Blossom Town's

558
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,760
Xuan paper industry and brand.

559
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,840
He has the duty and obligation

560
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:49,280
to publicly apologize in the media,

561
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:51,080
to minimize the damage.

562
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:51,960
Second,

563
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:53,720
if he refuses to apologize,

564
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:55,880
we can take legal action

565
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:57,240
to defend our reputation

566
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:58,240
and set the record straight.

567
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,000
Third,

568
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,520
Peach Blossom Town has the finest

569
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:02,680
Xuan paper culture and craftsmanship.

570
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,440
I suggest

571
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,240
we host a large-scale

572
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,720
Xuan paper cultural exchange event,

573
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,720
with full and positive publicity.

574
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:12,280
We can invite many industry insiders

575
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,840
to vindicate Peach Blossom Town,

576
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,240
and also help everyone better understand

577
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,280
our Xuan paper industry

578
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:17,800
and the profound Xuan paper culture.

579
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:20,080
Lin Yiran.

580
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,320
Secretary Peng. Secretary.

581
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:24,920
The county is now

582
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:27,320
deeply concerned about our next plan.

583
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:29,000
But from what I just heard,

584
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:31,560
your first two ideas won't work.

585
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:33,680
Master Jiang Ziliu

586
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:36,720
is highly respected in the art world.

587
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:37,760
Offending him

588
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:40,600
means offending the whole art world.

589
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,000
For our Peach Blossom Town,

590
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,760
it would have a huge negative impact.

591
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,520
What you just mentioned about holding

592
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:48,440
a Xuan paper cultural exchange event,

593
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:50,560
is like our Paper King Competition.

594
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:51,720
They mean the same thing.

595
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:52,520
Right.

596
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:54,680
What Paper King Competition?

597
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:55,840
Our Peach Blossom Town

598
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:57,440
used to hold the Paper King Competition.

599
00:22:57,840 --> 00:23:00,000
Papermakers nationwide would come.

600
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,200
For many consecutive years,

601
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,120
the Xuan family won the Paper King title.

602
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:05,280
It was discontinued later.

603
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:06,840
But the judges of the competition

604
00:23:06,840 --> 00:23:08,960
were all authorities in the industry.

605
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:09,760
And the participants

606
00:23:09,760 --> 00:23:12,040
were the top paper masters nationwide.

607
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,760
If this competition is revived

608
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,040
and our Peach Blossom Town wins again,

609
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:16,920
it would prove that paper made here

610
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:18,440
is the best Xuan paper in the country.

611
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:19,120
Right.

612
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:20,440
Director Liao,

613
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:22,520
can our Paper King Competition

614
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:24,240
be revived as soon as possible?

615
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:26,520
Me?

616
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:27,520
I'm to organize it?

617
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:28,000
That's right.

618
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:31,000
This, this isn't something I can do.

619
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:31,880
Secretary,

620
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:33,880
what's going on with you?

621
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,440
Secretary Peng, you know me.

622
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:37,440
Writing reports,

623
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:38,720
doing research, I can manage.

624
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:41,040
But organizing isn't my strong suit.

625
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:41,880
Director Liao,

626
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:44,520
you always drop the ball when it counts.

627
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:46,600
Usually, when I see you in the office

628
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,920
giving big lectures,

629
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:49,520
you've got more to say than anyone.

630
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:51,760
Tell me, can you do it or not?

631
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:54,440
Let me tell you,

632
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,040
if you can, then do it.

633
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:57,120
If not, step aside.

634
00:23:58,760 --> 00:23:59,440
Secretary Peng,

635
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:01,520
can the Paper King Competition prep

636
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:02,600
be entrusted to me?

637
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,200
Don't even think about it.

638
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:09,200
Reflect on what you've done.

639
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:10,560
And wait for disciplinary action.

640
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:12,440
Secretary Peng.

641
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:13,760
Before I took the civil service exam,

642
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:15,600
I worked at a Beijing event planning firm,

643
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,160
organizing large-scale events.

644
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:19,280
From initial planning to execution,

645
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:20,240
I was in charge of it all.

646
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,520
I have experience in this area.

647
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:24,240
And after all, this whole matter

648
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:25,600
started because of me.

649
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,160
It's my responsibility and duty

650
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,600
to minimize the damage.

651
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,480
Stop rambling.

652
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:31,920
This isn't your concern.

653
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,240
As for your work,

654
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,880
Secretary Peng has other plans.

655
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:39,120
If I get transferred over this,

656
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:39,920
I won't accept it.

657
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,400
If I mess up the Paper King Competition,

658
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,200
no disciplinary action will be needed.

659
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:46,480
I'll resign on my own.

660
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:48,600
Yiran, don't be rash.

661
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,160
Think it over.

662
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:49,960
Lin Yiran.

663
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:55,040
Are you making a solemn oath to me?

664
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:56,360
Yes.

665
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:57,560
Alright.

666
00:24:58,560 --> 00:24:59,880
This solemn oath of yours,

667
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:01,200
I accept it.

668
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:03,320
Secretary Peng,

669
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:06,840
the Paper King Competition is a big deal.

670
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:07,840
She can't handle it.

671
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:09,240
You take charge.

672
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:15,600
Me?

673
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,080
That's it.

674
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,240
This matter is settled.

675
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:20,440
Get the execution plan done

676
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:22,040
for the Paper King Competition ASAP.

677
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:22,640
Tomorrow.

678
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:24,760
I want it by tomorrow.

679
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:25,640
Let's go.

680
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:26,000
Okay.

681
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:27,520
Take care, Secretary.

682
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:32,240
No, Mom.

683
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:35,400
If she isn't training you enough,

684
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:37,200
just tell her directly, okay?

685
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:39,080
You're making me tell her.

686
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,480
You're making a simple thing complicated.

687
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,240
Mom, I'm not...

688
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:44,800
Hello?

689
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:55,480
Taozi

690
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,200
Didn't Director Liao ask you to do

691
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:58,080
the design draft for the official account?

692
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:58,840
You still haven't done it?

693
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:02,200
Many are nagging me. They have to wait.

694
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,360
I've still got a huge stack of reports.

695
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:07,480
Insurance forms,

696
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:09,000
Economic census, farmland surveys...

697
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:09,800
And more.

698
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,000
Tons of them.

699
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:13,400
What if you can't turn them in tomorrow?

700
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,120
I'll just tell him I have a stomachache.

701
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,280
He won't do anything to me.

702
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:19,560
Oh, right.

703
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:21,760
Let me tell you something serious.

704
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,600
I've been thinking about it.

705
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,480
Organizing this Paper King Competition

706
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:26,640
isn't really that hard.

707
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,760
The format already exists from before.

708
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:32,520
Just pick a large Xuan paper factory

709
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:34,240
to serve as the competition venue.

710
00:26:34,640 --> 00:26:36,600
Then set up subgroups underneath.

711
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:39,200
That's really all there is to it, right?

712
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:41,680
And as for staffing,

713
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:44,080
Secretary Peng can pull people to help.

714
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:44,960
Who would dare not listen?

715
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:45,600
Oh, you.

716
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:46,680
You're making it sound way too simple.

717
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,720
Hey, if you have something to say, say it.

718
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:50,680
Help me get a discount first, then I'll tell.

719
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:51,480
I've sent you the link.

720
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:52,440
Oh, come on,

721
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,280
you're dragging this out.

722
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:03,680
Now spill it.

723
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:06,600
Think about it.

724
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,760
When Peng put Director Liao in charge,

725
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,640
old Liao jolted as if struck by lightning.

726
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:12,760
Why?

727
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:14,960
Because in this whole thing,

728
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:16,040
there are tons of pitfalls.

729
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,680
It used to be held every year.

730
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:20,800
Why did they suddenly stop?

731
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,040
If you ask me,

732
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:28,760
you really do know your stuff.

733
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:30,520
Of course.

734
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:31,480
My parents

735
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,680
worked in the system most of their lives.

736
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:35,200
I grew up absorbing it all.

737
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:36,560
All the pitfalls you're stepping into,

738
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:38,120
they've already stepped into for me.

739
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:40,440
So that's why I say,

740
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,000
I'm the real newbie here.

741
00:27:42,440 --> 00:27:43,440
In the past,

742
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,720
whenever I organized any event,

743
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:47,040
I thought as long as I put in the effort,

744
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:48,600
I'd definitely see results.

745
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,520
But after coming over here...

746
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:53,320
Forget it.

747
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:54,240
I'll stop talking.

748
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:58,200
How should I put this?

749
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:01,520
This Paper King Competition

750
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,440
even if you give it your all,

751
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:05,520
you might not get a good outcome.

752
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:09,120
It's not too late to back out now.

753
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:12,040
Let me help you find a way out of it.

754
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:13,240
No need.

755
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:15,560
Once started, there's no turning back.

756
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:17,280
Otherwise you'd never get anything done.

757
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:19,000
But what if it really flops?

758
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,080
Would you actually quit?

759
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:26,200
Do you still have a fallback plan?

760
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:28,920
No.

761
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:31,360
After resigning from Beijing,

762
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,280
there's no fallback plan.

763
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:03,800
It's so big.

764
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:04,480
Right?

765
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:08,520
What do you think?

766
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:09,840
Way bigger than the Xuan family's, huh?

767
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:13,080
If we get this place as the venue,

768
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:13,840
that'd be amazing.

769
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:14,600
Exactly.

770
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:16,680
Mr. Xiao.

771
00:29:17,040 --> 00:29:18,560
Two from the Economic Development Office.

772
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:19,640
President Xiao.

773
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:21,800
Hello, Mr. Xiao.

774
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:23,000
I'm from the Economic Development Office.

775
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:23,760
Lin Yiran.

776
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,760
You two are now quite famous

777
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,400
in Peach Blossom Town.

778
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:32,080
Mr. Xiao, you're flattering us.

779
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:34,040
We're just a couple of small fries.

780
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,040
How could we compare to you?

781
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:35,520
Right.

782
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,000
We just toured your factory.

783
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:38,800
It's huge.

784
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:40,080
That's what I'm saying.

785
00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:41,320
Mr. Xiao really is something.

786
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:43,080
Worthy of the Xuan Paper Association head.

787
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:43,560
Right?

788
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:44,320
Not really.

789
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,240
The fellow tradesmen are just being kind.

790
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,240
Can't take it seriously.

791
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:51,160
So...

792
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:53,560
Mr. Xiao,

793
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:57,000
let's do the Paper King Competition here.

794
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:01,560
That really won't work.

795
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:03,080
You've seen it yourselves.

796
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:04,240
Right now,

797
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,960
I'm rushing an order worth millions.

798
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:07,960
If I can't deliver on time,

799
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:09,080
I'll have to pay penalties.

800
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,320
Um, Mr. Xiao,

801
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,240
could we work something out?

802
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,960
This really isn't something to work out.

803
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:17,480
Mr. Xiao,

804
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,960
you lead the Xuan Paper Association.

805
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:21,440
The Paper King Competition

806
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:23,520
is for our town's Xuan paper industry.

807
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:25,880
Director Liao really praised your place.

808
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,000
Secretary Peng supports it too.

809
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:27,800
Secretary Peng says your place is great.

810
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:28,360
Yes.

811
00:30:28,600 --> 00:30:30,080
Secretary Peng already met with us.

812
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:32,800
The Xuan Paper Association will support it.

813
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:33,480
But right now,

814
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:35,080
you've seen my actual situation.

815
00:30:35,080 --> 00:30:35,680
Right?

816
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:38,640
If you'd told me earlier,

817
00:30:38,640 --> 00:30:40,440
I just wouldn't have taken this order.

818
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,240
But now,

819
00:30:42,360 --> 00:30:43,440
there's really nothing I can do.

820
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:44,080
Yes, yes.

821
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:46,200
This was indeed an oversight on our part.

822
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,680
We apologize, we're sorry.

823
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,000
This isn't about apologies.

824
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:50,480
In business,

825
00:30:50,680 --> 00:30:52,080
you have to keep your word.

826
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:54,800
I must deliver the order on time.

827
00:30:56,040 --> 00:30:57,240
Anything else?

828
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,040
Come on, step aside.

829
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:04,240
Mr... Mr. Xiao.

830
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:10,800
If you ask me,

831
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:11,800
he's doing this on purpose.

832
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,920
Whoever hosts the Paper King Competition

833
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,160
gets the publicity.

834
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:17,160
His isn't the only big factory in town.

835
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:17,600
Exactly.

836
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:18,480
Why bother?

837
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:20,000
Why hang myself on one tree?

838
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:21,400
Right.

839
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:23,520
Let's find another tree to hang on.

840
00:31:30,320 --> 00:31:32,480
Leaders, this is my situation.

841
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:35,440
My factory, you see,

842
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:36,960
if it relied on selling Xuan paper,

843
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,520
would've starved long ago.

844
00:31:38,840 --> 00:31:40,040
You've seen it yourselves.

845
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:42,040
I've got plenty of paper-scooping vats,

846
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,560
but frankly speaking,

847
00:31:43,560 --> 00:31:44,960
they're all just for show.

848
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:46,960
False advertising.

849
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:48,000
When someone wants paper,

850
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,760
I go to Mr. Xiao's factory to get it.

851
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:52,000
When someone comes to visit,

852
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,320
I bring over Mr. Xiao's craftsmen

853
00:31:53,320 --> 00:31:54,760
to put on a little show.

854
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:58,040
Me, host the Paper King Competition?

855
